<p>Would it be possible to <strong>draw a vertical line across multiple</strong> <code>UITableViewCell</code>s with a gradual animation from top to bottom satisfying following requirements?</p>  <p>Requirements:</p>  <ol> <li>The line stays drawn after scrolling away and back to the 1st <code>UITableCellView</code></li> <li>Calling <code>[tableView reloadData]</code> with the animation in progress will not interrupt it</li> <li>Scrolling the <code>UITableView</code> with the animation in progress should be possible</li> <li>The line can have several empty segments (stop drawing in 3rd cell, continue with 5th)</li> <li>The line should be drawn on top of anything that is already drawn on the <code>UITableViewCell</code></li> </ol>  <p>Thank you for all the input and hints!</p>